hopobject.body: What's the interest rate on this account? al abeer medical center jeddah bawadi The airline expects a ruling from the UK competition commission on 13 August, which may see Ryanair ordered to sell down its stake in Aer Lingus. Millar said it was a "bizarre situation", and accused the commission of wasting "[British] taxpayer money investigating two Irish carriers". However, he said the airline would resist as long as possible in the hope it could eventually take over its Irish rival and pursue a "dual-brand strategy", likening its approach to manufacturers who sell "the same soap powder" for more money in different packaging.
